title: EFA, HYGH: Big ETF Outflows - Nasdaq.com
text: Looking at units outstanding versus one week prior within the universe of ETFs covered at ETF Channel, the biggest outflow was seen in the iShares MSCI EAFE ETF, where 11,400,000 units were destroyed, or a 1.2% decrease week over week. Among the largest underlying components of EFA, in morning trading today NXP Semiconductors is up about 4.5%, and Check Point Software Technologies is higher by about 2.1%.    makeArticleAd();  And on a percentage change basis, the ETF with the biggest outflow was the iShares Interest Rate Hedged High Yield Bond ETF, which lost 450,000 of its units, representing a 24.3% decline in outstanding units compared to the week prior.
